.TH "nanddev_mtd_max_bad_blocks" 9 "nanddev_mtd_max_bad_blocks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nanddev_mtd_max_bad_blocks \- Get the maximum number of bad eraseblock on a specific region of the NAND device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nanddev_mtd_max_bad_blocks
.BI "(struct mtd_info *mtd "  ","
.BI "loff_t offs "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd" 12
MTD device
.IP "offs" 12
offset of the NAND region
.IP "len" 12
length of the NAND region
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Default implementation for mtd->\fB_max_bad_blocks\fP. Only works if
nand->memorg.max_bad_eraseblocks_per_lun is > 0.
.SH "RETURN"
a positive number encoding the maximum number of eraseblocks on a
portion of memory, a negative error code otherwise.
